itunes:summary:
Derek Weida is joined by 13 year old weightlifter Brooklyn Sittner and her father Cory to discuss what is was like getting into weightlifting at such an early age, her father Cory opens up about his time in prison and how it has shaped his mentality on life and what is taken for granted, and the two explain how they work together on the road during competitions.
